me of a forested region on the borders between northeastern France and eastern Belgium. The second derives from Old English <i>hēah</i> ‘high’ + <i>worthign</i> ‘enclosed settlement’."],"variants":[{"name":"Harden","meanings":["English: variant of   Arden   with prosthetic <i>H-</i>.","English: habitational name, either from Haredene Wood in East Tisbury (Wiltshire), or from Haredon (in Ugborough, Devon). The first placename probably derives from Old English <i>hara</i> ‘hare’ + <i>denu</i> ‘valley’. The second is from Old English <i>hara</i> + <i>dūn</i> ‘hare hill’.","English: variant of   Harding  ."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":5,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":14,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Peter Ardene was born in 1323, in England. He had at least 1 daughter with Ceicily De Bury. He died in 1379, in his hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1323–1379":"1323–1379","1327–1387":"1327–1387","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1428":"1428","1328":"1328","England":"England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"1323–1379":"1323–1379","1327–1387":"1327–1387","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1428":"1428","1328":"1328","England":"England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"1323–1379":"1323–1379","1327–1387":"1327–1387","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1428":"1428","1328":"1328","England":"Angleterre","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir Peter Ardene est né en 1323, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Ceicily De Bury. Il est décédé en 1379, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 56 ans."},"de":{"1323–1379":"1323–1379","1327–1387":"1327–1387","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1428":"1428","1328":"1328","England":"England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","lifeSummary":"Sir Peter Ardene wurde 1323 in England geboren. Er hatte mit Ceicily De Bury mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1379 im Alter von 56 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1323–1379":"1323–1379","1327–1387":"1327–1387","1368–1428":"1368–1428","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1428":"1428","1328":"1328","Englan